Timbre Analyze Toolset

Overview: Command-line tool `timbre-analyze` for audio timbre segmentation, clustering, and visualization.

Quick Start

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Example Commands

```bash
timbre-analyze \
  --in_dir /path/to/audio \
  --sr 22050 \
  --pre_emphasis 0.97 \
  --frame 46ms --hop 10ms \
  --features mfcc,delta,delta2,chroma,scflux \
  --seg_method novelty \
  --seg_kernel_gauss 3.0 \
  --beat_sync on \
  --min_seg_beats 2 \
  --cluster_method gmm \
  --k_policy auto \
  --k_min 4 --k_max 12 \
  --k_select bic \
  --smooth hmm --hmm_selfbias 0.6 \
  --label_scheme global \
  --palette "A:#E53935,B:#FB8C00,C:#FDD835,D:#43A047,E:#1E88E5,F:#8E24AA,G:#6D4C41,H:#00ACC1" \
  --seq_distance levenshtein \
  --dist_distribution jsd \
  --dist_markov frobenius \
  --alpha 0.6 \
  --embed umap --embed_dim 2 \
  --out_dir /path/to/results
```

